Women’s Volleyball: Long Beach State Sweeps UC Irvine in First Round of Big West Tournament
The Long Beach State women's volleyball team decisively defeated UC Irvine 3-0 in the first round of the Big West Tournament, showcasing their home advantage at the LBS Financial Credit Union Pyramid. The Beach notched their third win over the Anteaters this season, winning the sets 25–18, 25–20, and 26–24. Coach Natalie Reagan praised the team's strong performance and focus against a resilient UC Irvine squad. Key contributions came from Elise Agi, who led with 12 kills, and Logan King, who added 11 kills and a .435 hitting percentage. This victory extends LBSU's home winning streak to 11 matches.
By the Numbers- Long Beach State won 25–18, 25–20, 26–24 against UC Irvine.
- Logan King had 11 kills at .435 hitting; Elise Agi recorded 12 kills at .250 hitting.
- LBSU has secured 11 straight home victories this season.
- The Beach will host Cal Poly in the semifinals on Friday at 6 PM.
- UC Irvine managed to tie the third set 18-18 after trailing earlier.
- Post-match, attention shifts to the serving and passing game against Cal Poly's offense.
Long Beach State aims to build on this momentum against Cal Poly, focusing on execution in serves and passes to manage their opponent's strong offense. The matchup will be crucial for advancing further in the tournament.
Bottom LineThe commanding victory reaffirms Long Beach State's dominance at home and sets them up as serious contenders in the Big West Tournament. Their performance, especially from key players, highlights their potential to win the championship.
